{"add":{"doc":{"id":"d004fb93e2934957bed261fe7a89e27228ea6e5cd096dde6ee7a0cae3cc751eb","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Ghana_satellite.jpg/220px-Ghana_satellite.jpg","previous":[],"after":["Satellite Internet service provides fixed, portable, and mobile Internet access. It is among the most expensive forms of broadband Internet access, but may be the only choice available in remote areas.[64] Data rates range from 2 kbit/s to 1 Gbit/s downstream and from 2 kbit/s to 10 Mbit/s upstream. Satellite communication typically requires a clear line of sight, will not work well through trees and other vegetation, is adversely affected by moisture, rain, and snow (known as rain fade), and may require a fairly large, carefully aimed, directional antenna."]}}}